Town halls have failed to recalibrate some of the 100,000 ticket machines in the UK
making it impossible for drivers to pay the exact cost of parking
Nationwide there are 100,000 parking meters yet several councils are still yet to upgrade them to accept the three-year-old 5p and 10p coins
This is because their hourly charges often end in 5p and 10p yet the machines do not accept new five or 10p coins
